02/03/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The verdict in the case of nine former police officers on trial for the1992 illegal deportation of Bosniak civilians from Montenegro will be delivered on March 29th. 
Both prosecutors and defence attorneys wrapped up their closing arguments Tuesday (March 1st). 
The defendants told the court they are not guilty, as all they did was follow orders. 
Over 79 Bosniaks were handed over to Bosnian Serbs, who killed most of them. 
(Pcnen, Radio Free Europe - 01/03/11)
